{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὄρθρος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>the time just before</b> or <b>about daybreak, dawn, cock-crow</b> (ἀπ᾽ ὄρθρου μέχρι περ ἂν ἥλιος ἀνάσχῃ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 951d), τάχα δ᾽ ὄ. ἐγίγνετο δημιοεργός “hymnus ad Mercurium” 98; ἐπειδὰν ὄ. ᾖ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 256, compare “Av.” 496, etc.; ὄρθρου \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>at dawn,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 577, 4th c.BC: Sopater Comicus 25, 4th c.BC: Aristopho Comicus 10; ὄρθρου γενομένου 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.198; ἅμα ὄρθρῳ [prev. author] 7.188, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.112, etc.; ἐς ὄρθρον 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 18.56, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 6.6; κατ᾽ ὄρθρον 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 772; περὶ ὄρθρον 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.101 (compare περίορθρος) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πρὸς ὄρθρον towards <b>dawn,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 1089; πρὸς ὄρθρον γ᾽ ἐστίν [prev. author] “Ec.” 20; ὑπ᾽ ὄρθρον Batrachomyomachia 103; ὑπὸ τὸν ὄ. 2nd-3rd c.AD: Dio Cassius Historicus 76.17 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν ὄ., <i>absolutely</i>, <b>in the morning,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.181 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δι᾽ ὄρθρων each <b>morning early,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 909 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὄ. βαθύς dim <b>morning twilight,</b> ἀλλὰ νῦν ὄ. β. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 216, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 43a, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 18.14; τῆς παρελθούσης νυκτὸς.., ἔτι βαθέος ὄ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 310a, cf. NT.Luke.24.1. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>Ὄρθρος</b